2. **Profile builder is incomplete against frozen schema.** Missing must-haves: `name`, `marital_status`, `kids_count`, `height_cm`, `weight_kg` (the last two feed BMI, which Preventive Planner depends on). Missing all 5 lifestyle good-to-haves: smoking, alcohol, exercise frequency, dietary preference, sleep hours.
3. **Recovery Guidance sidebar placement is ambiguous.** Frozen design: Recovery Guidance sits in its own visually separated tier, below a divider, still a primary module (not grouped with Profile/Settings). Latest status summary described it grouped with "Profile, Recovery Guidance, and Settings" as if all three are equal-weight utility items — needs confirmation of what was actually built.
4. **Accordion null-handling unverified.** Frozen rule: `why_not` / `alternatives` / `trade_offs` render as expandable sections ONLY when non-null; a null field must render no section at all, never an empty/greyed one. Term/Prescription Explainer likely returns null for several of these fields regularly — confirm this isn't silently showing empty boxes.
5. **Profile persistence strategy** — currently local React state. Confirm this is understood as a temporary scaffold and not a fallback destination (e.g. localStorage) that quietly becomes "good enough" instead of the frozen Supabase + RLS design.

