## 🔒 Frozen Constraints (do not violate without explicit human sign-off)

- Free/open-source only for anything in the deployed/production path — no paid APIs, DBs, auth, OCR. (Dev-tooling AI assistance, e.g. Antigravity, is fine — production API keys are not shared/paid.)
- No history/log feature anywhere — no per-search logs for Insurance Advisor, Preventive Planner, or Term/Prescription Explainer. Only `profiles` and `recovery_items` persist.
- No diagnostic, predictive, or treatment-prescribing language/UI, ever.
- Input fields mapped to real data boundaries (age, budget_band, city, gender, etc.) must be dropdown/constrained — free text only allowed for Term/Prescription Explainer's input field.
- Checklist mutual exclusivity ("None of the above" disables the other 14, and vice versa) is shared logic across `family_history` and `existing_conditions` — one reusable component, not two.
- Sidebar/top nav are fixed; module switching happens inline in the main content area only — no modals, no route changes for this.
- Buttons: only one solid/primary CTA visible per screen at a time.
- Badges: exactly 3 tones (teal-good, amber-caution, gray-neutral) — no 4th tone without deliberate design decision.
- Warm Harbor palette + Fraunces/Inter typography, as specified in the original frontend prompt.